column7:
OPC 26.33 V
Multinet 9.21 V
Walkie-talkies full
Vemco Bay chargin
CTD 8.8 V

Glider programmed to go to northern waypoint during testing, then turn around for mission
Issues: cradle got caught in too-long rope loop -> tagline on cart next time!

Dive to 5 m and resurface (11:25)
Retrieved float (11:36)
Dive to 15 m and resurface (11:43)
Compass calibrations (11:55)

Mission abort at 19:25 ADT if we don't quit early
Initial dive to 60m -- after resurfacing, check AZFP, readjust deep inflection point, start cage/net
Mission start proper: 14:07
Boat echosounder was interfering with glider

54 kHz fish tag
Deployed to 107 m
Scant amounts of plankton in nets

Not enough biomass for cryo
Sample jar #s 207492-207496
Roughly 50 mins processing time

Multinet 8.9 V
CTD 8.7 V
OPC 26.01 V

Swapped Seabird battery (took out battery B, replaced with battery SB)
SB voltage 11.3 V

Reviewed files from connection w/ SBER and it says that "dv/dt step change" when voltage less than 8.7 V. This was the issue why NO data was collected yesterday
NEW CUTOFF 9V
Tow line attached to cart this time, no issues with cart

Bottom of nets dragged along seaflor; reset and try again
No data

Swapped out OPC battery #3
Battery 3 lasted 14 casts before needing a charge. Charged to 28.25 V
Swapped in battery #2 @ 26.7 V
Kim on whale watch in GMB

200 kHz echosounder shows layer of likely copepods at 30-60 m
Layer does not appear on 38, 75, or 130 kHz echosounders, so likely copepods
Captain says layer disappeared 2-3 miles back

Second probable-copepod layer at 100m depth, in addition to 30-60m layer
Jude in and out of signal, Fox has no service, sat phone works in wheelhouse

200 kHz echosounder momentarily turned on to check copepod layers; 20-50 m and 90-110m layers
Kim has picture of echosounder
Echosounder off at 10:50 ADT
One breaching humpback spotted in distance
Pinger says max of 153m; check CTD data for recorded depth + compare

Layer from 0-40m at 200 kHz; little bit at 100m
Echosounder off at 14:49 ADT

Fiddled with depth pinger to determine how to stop running the net into the ground
Undershot unlocking depth -> nets did not fire

Swapped OPC battery 2 for battery 3
Batt 2 swapped @ 25.95 V
Batt 3 @ 26.85 V
Multinet 9V; CTD batt 11.7 V

Kim off whale watch
No whales sighted
Communication cable for OPC had battery swapped
Aborted tow @ 12:19 due to improperly programmed depths. Redeployed at 12:29

OPC battery check - 26.43 V
CTD battery check - 12.4 V
Downloaded CTD data

Water depth: 186m
OPC + CTD off at 13:13
Brief mishap with cart but glider successfully deployed
Deployed to 140m; bottom depth 148m (overshot a bit)
